title: nazokake
body:
なぞかけ 
Nazokake is a type of riddle involving two things that seem to have nothing in common, but can be linked by some word play. 

An English example:  "What do mini skirts and wedding speeches have in common? The shorter they are, the happier they make other people." 

In Japanese, nazokake normally follow the following format: 

* ○○とかけて××と解く。その心は□□。 

In this case, ○○ and ×× are two seemingly unrelated things, while □□ is the punchline that connects them. 


h4. See also 

* [[pun]] 


h4. Links 

* "Wikipedia entry (Japanese)":http://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%81%AA%E3%81%9E%E3%81%8B%E3%81%91

title: burakawani_(ooo_combo)
body:
One of [[Kamen Rider OOO]]'s final combos, accessed via the Cobra, Turtle (Kame), and Gator (Wani) Core Medals. This combo is only exclusive to the Kamen Rider OOO Wonderful movie.

BuraKaWani's body is covered in a substance called Sooma Venom, which makes him able to heal instantly after taking any attack. As OOO BuraKaWani, OOO's eyesight is doubled and gains infra-red vision via the Cobra Head, use the turtle shell-like Goura Guardner via the Kame Arms, and use the Saw Deadscythers on his legs to generate an energy crocodile, which chomps his enemies with every kick via the Wani Legs.

In addition, he is armed with the Burangi, which lets him summon a giant cobra from the "[[ponytail]]" on the back of his head to attack enemies. It is possible the orange Core Medals can be used for Random changes, but it is unknown if that is certain, as the Cores appeared for only one movie.

His Scanning Charge is the Warning Ride where OOO projects three orange rings in front of him before dashing through them in a foot-first slide before unleashing a powerful kick with the Saw Deadscythers, which generate a giant energy crocodile head to bite through the target.

title: tamashii_(ooo_combo)
body:
One of [[Kamen Rider OOO]]'s combos, accessed via the Hawk (Taka), Imagin, and Shocker Core Medals. This combo is only exclusive to the Let's Go Kamen Riders movie.

His Scanning Charge is the Tamashii Bomber, where OOO executes by first gathering energy between his hands, which changes into the symbol of the Shocker Medal. He then launches the symbol at his opponent, and the symbol attaches itself to the chest of the opponent, and as it does, OOO gathers energy in either hand, which form the Taka and Imagin Medal symbols, respectively, and then launches them at the opponent. The three symbols then merge into the symbol of the TaMaShii combo and then explode.

title: pineapple_day
body:
Pineapple Day is August 17, or 8/17. 

In Japanese, each single-digit number has at least a few different sounds associated with it. Using these sounds, people can create phrases from a given set of numbers. In this case, 8/17 becomes "paina" (8=pa 1=i 7=na). "Paina" [パイナ] is the beginning of the word "painappuru" [パイナップル], or "pineapple". 

For more of these types of days, see "here":http://qjphotos.wordpress.com/2010/08/17/happy-pineapple-day/.

title: takekushi_meguru
body:
An [[original]] character by [[Rakurakutei Ramen]]. 

A magician who is made an apprentice of [[Kamishiro Seren]], and a relatively late-coming member of the regular cast.  

She is clumsy, poor at housework, and incapable of controlling her magic well enough to use low-level magic.  For her, it's high-level magic, or nothing.  Supposedly, this puts her on the same general level as Seren, who needs a magic item to dampen her magic enough to cast low-level magic, and she has the potential to become a great mage.

Living with the rest of the Karindou cast, she often has trouble with [[ujintoki_ginka|Ginka]], who is overtly a lesbian, while Meguru... is not.

She also has a history with [[Ujikintoki Tamaryu]] as a party member in a game made that was never released to the wider public, but which is referenced by the Karin-dou 4Koma, anyway.

She now teaches class at the school that Tamaryu goes to.

title: charles_darwin
body:
An English naturalist born on 12 February 1809. He established that all species of life have descended over time from common ancestors, and proposed the scientific theory that this branching pattern of evolution resulted from a process that he called natural selection, in which the struggle for existence has a similar effect to the artificial selection involved in selective breeding.

He died on 19 April 1882 when he was diagnosed with what was called “angina pectoris” which then meant coronary thrombosis and disease of the heart. At the time of his death, the physicians diagnosed “anginal attacks”, and “heart-failure”.

title: neo_geo_pocket_color
body:
A 16-bit color handheld video game console manufactured by [[SNK]]. It is the successor to SNK's monochrome Neo Geo Pocket handheld which debuted in 1998 in Japan. The Neo Geo Pocket Color was released on March 16, 1999 in Japan, August 6, 1999 in North America, and some time in 1999 in Europe.

The Neo Geo Pocket Color was SNK's last video game console, and is backwards compatible with the Neo Geo Pocket. In 2000, following SNK's purchase by American pachinko manufacturer Aruze, the Neo Geo Pocket Color was dropped from both the North American and European markets. It did, however, last until 2001 in Japan, with a total of 2 million units sold.

title: catherine_(rakurakutei_ramen)
body:
An [[original]] character by [[Rakurakutei Ramen]].

Classmate with [[ujikintoki_tamaryu|Tamaryu]] and [[ran_straherz|Ran]], and whose teacher is [[kagurazaki_shizuki|Shizuki]] in the new Youkai school that opens up,  she appears in the school-related strips.  She appears more often as the school becomes a more prominent feature of the series.

"Catherine" is her nickname based upon the fact that she is the mixed-blood daughter of a canine youkai and a fire bird youkai--the kanji for "fire" "bird" "dog" can be pronounced like "Ka-Tori-Inu", or how a Japanese person would say "Catherine".  Her actual name is Inukai Suzume.

As a fire-bird-dog, she has an unusual body with large wing-arms, dog-ears, a tail, and apparently a weakness against water.

title: shiraishi_sara
body:
An [[original]] character by [[Rakurakutei Ramen]]. 

Classmate with [[ujikintoki_tamaryu|Tamaryu]] and [[ran_straherz|Ran]], and whose teacher is [[kagurazaki_shizuki|Shizuki]] in the new Youkai school that opens up,  she occasionally appears in class-related strips. 

She is a white serpent youkai, probably a reference to "The Legend of the White Snake (Wikipedia)":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legend_of_the_White_Snake, and claims as her lover the rather unusual target of a frog-youkai boy.  (This, in turn, is a reference to the Japanese belief in a rock-paper-scissors balance of frogs being weak against snakes, who enjoy eating frogs, while slugs are strong against snakes and weak to frogs.)  

Sara enjoys talking about "eating" her "lover", Yanagiba Kiyoshi, in ways that one can only hope is suggestive. 

She has a [[lamia]]'s figure, and apparently goes without wearing underwear with distressing frequency.  However, there's (usually) nothing there to see, and her belly scales cover anything up, so she apparently thinks nothing of going bottomless (even swimming without a bottom).

title: ikkyuusan
body:
Ikkyū-san (一休さん) is an anime based on the historical Zen Buddhist monk Ikkyū that follows his mischievous adventures as a child during his stay at Ankoku Temple. In each episode, Ikkyū relies on his intelligence and wit to solve all types of problems, from distraught farmers to greedy merchants.

The anime was well received by all ages in Japan and throughout Asia, as it didn't rely on violence. Even when violence appears, it is usually presented in a mild or necessary way (for example, there are occasional references to the Ōnin War).

A running gag of Ikkyū-san is that whenever Ikkyū is trying to think of a plan, he sits in a lotus position, wets his two index fingers, and rotates them above his head.

title: lilith_(drowtales)
body: Lilith is one of the few original characters in Drowtales: the Space Age. She is also arguably the main character of said story. Though there is some leeway when assigning who is or isn't the main character of that particular story archive. Afterall there are some pretty powerful key characters from the main archive that have appeared in the Space Age story. That said, Lilith continues to be the one around whom most of the other characters gather. She was the first main character in the story to be introduced, and she is the longest running main character to still be in the story. Therefore the arguments in favor of her being the main character are pretty substantial.

title: fusou_(battleship)
body:
"扶桑":http://www.pixiv.net/search.php?s_mode=s_tag&word=%E6%89%B6%E6%A1%91%20%E6%88%A6%E8%89%A6 (ふそう) 

A [[battleship]] of the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]], whose name comes from an archaic appelation for Japan. 

Its problematic linear arrangement of its six 14-inch twin-gun turrets limited its speed and defensive abilities. 
Although its mast was of a simple tripod type completion, it was later remodeled through repeated trial and error to become the highest and most distinctive of the “pagoda” masts that typified Japanese battleships of the period. 
With further upgrades bringing the addition of a seaplane catapult above the third turret, the guns' cruising position was changed to face forward. However, this caused instability on the bridge. This wouldn't change, even after the catapult had been relocated to the warship's stern, and formed an outwardly clear point of difference between Fusou and its sister ship, [[yamashiro_(battleship)|Yamashiro]]. 

Fusou was taken out of action by hits from 4 torpedoes from "an American destroyer":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Melvin_%28DD-680%29 during "the battle of Surigao Strait.":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Surigao_Strait#The_Battle_of_Surigao_Strait_.2825_October.29 The old battleship experienced a massive explosion approximately 20 minutes later, its hull ripping in two pieces down the middle. Not a single sailor aboard survived.

title: rukia_moon
body:
ルキア・ムーン

Character from [[Shinrabanshou]]. Introduced in the Shingoku Chapter as a mysterious human girl observing the main character [[maxi_(shinrabanshou)|Maxi]], but is later revealed to be a demon tasked by the last Rashin Emperor to search for his descendant, [[san_morte_(shinrabanshou)|San Morte]]. When she and [[Dirculum]] find Morte in the following Ougarasen Chapter, Rukia wants to protect the her while Dirculum wants to use her as a figurehead and take over the world. Their differences cause Rukia to leave Dirculum's side and join up with Maxi to defeat her.

Rukia goes by the title of Moonlight King, though she has no subordinates or even family, leaving her with the freedom to do whatever she wants. She's old friends with [[shirokarasuou_kurooshe|Kurooshe]] and always butted heads with Dirculum even before the San Morte incident.

Her name is derived from "Lucia", a latin name derived from the word for "light", referencing her title. However, "Moon" is only given as her last name once and may be a false name as part of her human disguise.

title: kagari_shuusei
body: [b]Kagari Shuusei (縢 秀星)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]], one of the Enforcers in Unit One of the Public Safety Bureau's Criminal Investigation Division. The youngest of the group after [[Tsunemori Akane]], he has been a latent criminal since his early childhood. As a result Kagari seems to not have grown up, and constantly tells jokes and teases people. He also keeps dinsoaur toys and jelly beans on his desk, and is interested in cooking. He is also a very able fighter in hand-to-hand combat, able to easily kill enemies bigger than him. He also harbors a hate for normal society and Sybil, but is loyal to his friends and despises those who would kill others out of a sense of superiority. [spoiler]In episode 16 he witnesses the true nature of Sybil, and is promptly killed by a cyborg under Sybil's control.[/spoiler]

title: karanomori_shion
body: [b]Karanomori Shion (唐之杜 志恩)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]], a Latent Criminal working with Unit One as their information analyst. Shion is very good with computer systems and is crucial in assisting Unit One during their investigations. She is frequently seen smoking and enjoys teasing [[Tsunemori Akane]]. [[Kougami Shin'ya]] and [[Kagari Shuusei]] have flatteringly nicknamed her "The Godess of Information Analysis". She is in a relationship with [[Kunizuka Yayoi]].

title: kougami_shin'ya
body: [b]Kougami Shin'ya (狡噛 慎也)[/b] is the main male character of [[Psycho-Pass]], an Enforcer of Unit One. At first seen as a violent man who disposes of anyone deemed a criminal by any means necessary, he is shaken by [[Tsunemori Akane]]'s sense of justice and her using the Dominator against him to prevent him from killing a rape victim deemed a criminal, Kougami changes. A calm and collected man, he is also extremely good at figuring out the threads behind crimes and is frequently the one who solves the cases. He is well built, and is an expert martial artist. He is also quite knowledgeable in literature. After the events of the first episode, he and Akane quickly become somewhat close and care about each other. It is revealed that [spoiler]he was an Inspector in the past alongside Nobuchika Ginoza, but the death of an Enforcer under his command (Sasayama) in a horrible murder led him to obsessing over catching the perpetrator, and as a result of too much insight into criminal minds, he was deemed a Latent Criminal by Sibyl and demoted into an Enforcer. He hates Makishima Shogo for his role in Sasayama's death.[/spoiler].

title: kunizuka_yayoi
body: [b]Kunizuka Yayoi (六合塚 弥生)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]], the only female Enforcer of Unit One. Always calm in the face of emergencies or horrible sights, she generally teams up with [[Ginoza Nobuchika]] and [[Kagari Shuusei]]. She used to be a guitar player before she was designated a Latent Criminal. She is in a relationship with [[Karanomori Shion]].

title: lawgiver
body:
A fictional futuristic looking [[handgun]] from the [[Judge Dredd]] stories in the [[2000 AD]] comics anthology and the 2012 [[Dredd]] film.

The [b]Lawgiver[/b] is the standard street judge personal weapon. It responds to voice commands thanks to its built-in advanced micro[[computer]] and can also fire several different types of ammunition, which include sound-suppresed [[bullet]]s, standard bullets, armor piercing bullets, incendiary bullets, full-auto, semi-auto and single-action bullets, 2-shot arc [i]"Double Wavy"[/i] bullets, high explosive rounds and electric discharge stunning rounds. 

The Lawgiver also has an advanced "[[DNA]] check" user verification system that only allows the owner of the gun to fire it.

title: easy_chair
body:

There may be some overlap between what is a large easy chair and what is a small couch. When in doubt tag the image as just a [[couch]].

title: patio_swing
body:
A piece of outdoor furniture that is composed of a [[bench]] or bench-like seat that is suspended above the ground using ropes, chains, or metal bars.  This allows the seat to be able to be rocked back and forth.

These pieces of furniture may be suspended using a temporary support structure, a permanent support structure, or may be fastened to the ceiling of a porch.

title: ball_chair
body:
A [[chair]] that is in the shape of a ball or sphere.  Some types are suspended in the air using ropes or chains, while others stand up using a base.

Oval or egg shaped ones are sometimes called an "egg chair," though another type of chair is also called that.
